<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1916-02-21T18:23:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1916-02-21T18:23:00-05:00" n="910" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d910">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 312.11/7353</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">Consul <persName type="from">Hostetter</persName> to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">American Consulate</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Hermosillo</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1916-02-21T16:00:00-07:23">
                                    <hi rend="italic">February 21, 1916, 4 p.m.</hi>
                                </date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>Department’s February 19, 6 p.m. In response to wire to General Serrano
                            who is conducting campaign against the Yaquis, says that as result of
                            the campaign against the Yaquis the valley is at present perfectly safe,
                            settlers having ample protection. Claims the campaign is being
                            vigorously pushed; has sufficient troops to protect that region.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Hostetter</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>